results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows giving the factorization of n into factors q(i) = prime(i)/i, i > 0.
comment: Row n is the multiset of Matula-Goebel numbers of all proper terminal subtrees of the rooted tree with Matula-Goebel number n. For example, the rooted tree with Matula-Goebel number 1362 is (o(o)((oo)(oo))), with proper terminal subtrees {o,o,o,o,o,o,(o),(oo),(oo),((oo)(oo))}, which have Matula-Goebel numbers {1,1,1,1,1,1,2,4,4,49}, which is row 1362, as required.
example: For example, row 65 is {1,1,1,2,2,3,6} because 65 = q(1)^3 q(2)^2 q(3) q(6).
